commit_message:
Refactoring/cleanup of Command classes.

TargetTool (now TargetCommand) had a semi-complex constructor that had
to forward arguments to argparse, but also stole some.  Now, the
optional stuff is enabled/configured using methods.

In addition, there's now a helper function (make command) that replaces
the complexity of the constructor.

commit_message:
Implicitly add components as they're needed.

The original design required having all components passed to a
DependencyManager, but this won't work in practice.  The implicit method
permits adding component tasks as they're needed, so resolvers can still
deal with only requested components but resolve their dependencies.

commit_message:
Track dependencies from beginning to end

The previous version of calculate_dependencies tracked dependencies
based on components, so there was no way to figure out which tasks were
required to meet the dependencies of initial targets.  To try and do
only the minimal work required (trying to consider weird projects where
multiple logical components may use a single checkout), the initial work
is seeded with all requested tasks.  As dependencies are tracked,
they're tracked based on the speciic dependent task, not the dependent
component.

commit_message:
Work on #9 - Support continuing after a failure

Task queues now support marking tasks as failed.  This method will
recursively remove any tasks that depend on the failed task, so nothing
that depends on failed tasks will be available during task resolution.

commit_message:
Try to cleanup command execution code

The code is a mess since it's trying to handle too much.  Task execution
probably needs to be rethought, but this code should at least be simpler
to follow and maintain.

  - The method to handle task failures is chosen once.  This avoids
    branching every time a task fails since the decision will always be
    the same.
  - It's easier to support more types of task failure handlers in the
    future.  I don't want to support too many, but at least the infra is
    there now.
  - All the actual execution takes place in a new method.  This should
    keep the setup separate from execution.
